Description_lang: Gronnlings are a menace to the region.  We should partner with the Frostwolf clan to thin the population.  One may even join our cause...
It would be a worthwhile endeavor to search the ship we escaped Tanaan Jungle in, it's bound to turn up something useful!
Gronnling bones have been discovered in the cavern behind the garrison. Your alchemists are interested in digging them up for research purposes.
The Grimfrost Ogres east of the Icewind Drifts are blatantly mistreating frostwolves.  Unacceptable!
There are reports of a bloody massacre on the Stonefury Cliffs!  Scatter the Frostbeak Scavengers and rescue wounded allies!
A scout has located a cache of Thunderlord potions frozen in the snow. Recovering them will allow your alchemists to learn about the ingredients of Draenor.
Grab all the loots
This is Matt's test mission *bugles and horns blair a triumphant tune*
Rylaks from the Burning Glacier have been attacking our supply caravans.  The material must flow!
Bladespire ogres on the Burning Glacier usually carry packs of supplies when they venture out into the dunes of Frostfire. They may contain new types of potions.
Run away!!
Kill the orcs in the mountains.
Kill the ogres in the desert.
Kill the undead in the snow.
Kill the arakkoa underground.
Kill the beasts in the jungle.
Kill the demons in the forest.
Kill the breakers in the town.
Kill the furies in the swamp.
Kill the primals in the plains.

Name_lang: One Mission To Rule Them All
Description_lang: The sword of a thousand truths must be destroyed in the Blackrock Foundry.  Make it happen dawg.
A regular patrol around the garrison seems like a good idea...
Corrupted beasts continue to plague the Cursed Woods. The Starfall Sentinels request our aid in putting the poor creatures out of their misery.
We could send several of our best on a raid of the Thunderlord outpost of Colossal's Fall!  Go forth to victory.
It's best not to lose a bet with the janitor.
It would be a worthwhile endeavor to search the ship we escaped Tanaan Jungle in, it's bound to turn up something useful!
A regular patrol around the garrison seems like a good idea...
Lunarfall Ravens from Moonflower Valley have been attacking our supply caravans.  The material must flow!
We could send several of our best on a raid of the Shadowmoon outpost of Shaz'Gul!  For the Alliance!
Arcane Anomalies are endangering the Fey Dragons of the Shimmer Mor.  Unacceptable!
The Shadowmoon have taken several Rangari and Alliance forces captive.  Infiltrate and rescue!
The gronn and the ogres are working together on a two-pronged attack. We must disrupt their machinations before they overwhelm us.
If there are design flaws in the Blackrock clan's war machines, we can disable them. Break in and inspect the war machines for weaknesses.
Draenor can count the genesaur among its most vicious creatures. We must contain them before they spread from Gorgrond to other areas.
We would like to leave the vicious arakkoa alone, but capturing their temple in the Spires of Arak would give us a strategic advantage.
Abyssals, the minions of Sargeras, are roaming the forests of Talador, setting them ablaze. Destroy them before the forest is ash.
Many of the rescued draenei prisoners have gone missing, and we think the saberon are to blame. Go investigate, but go well armed.
With infernals and felguard invading Talador, the rest of the Burning Legion can't be far behind. Defeat them, and try to find their source.
The voidlords and voidcallers plaguing Shadowmoon Valley are being summoned by someone. Find and kill whoever is responsible.
Magnaron and goren both grow rocky plates on their hides that have magical properties. Collect these plates for our use.
Numerous and powerful, ogre warlords are formidable allies of the Iron Horde. Try to induce them to leave - forcefully, if necessary.
To weaken the Thunderlord clan, we must eliminate their fiercest warriors - their clefthoof-riders. Go to their camp and free their mounts.
Fel magic has corrupted a few ancients of Shadowmoon Valley. They must be cut down to end their mad rampages.
The Warsong clan is a symbol of the Iron Horde's power. Under the cover of night, set its camp ablaze. This will kill their morale.
Patrols have reported that roving bands of saberon are waylaying merchants traveling through Nagrand. Find them and stop them.
Arakkoa talonpriests have begun sacrificing draenei to their god, Terokk. Interrupt their ritual and free the prisoners.
In a remote corner of Talador, a small faction of draenei has embraced the worship of Sargeras. Stop their cult before it spreads.
Ogre slavers have captured many of the draenei displaced by the Iron Horde. Send someone to their camp and liberate them.
Without their leader, the high ogre attack our spies warned us about will fail. Send an assassin to kill their warlord in Nagrand.
The hardened bark of the genesaur and botani offer an opportunity to strengthen our armor.  Do what needs to be done.
Pests! These ravagers are everywhere - in our supplies, in our barracks! Eradicate their nest in the Spires of Arak before they overrun us.
Infernals are an uncommon sight in Talador. We'd like to keep it that way. The more that are destroyed, the better.
Basilisks have turned some arakkoa in the Spires of Arak to stone. It's macabre, but this stone is a precious resource. Gather it carefully.
A group of territorial elementals has claimed an area near our supply route in Frostfire Ridge. Slay them and collect any lost supplies.
Dark magic runs amok in Shadowmoon Valley, giving rise to maddened, unnatural creatures. End their suffering.
Shadowmoon spellcasters are experimenting with unstable void magic near the Teluuna Observatory. Because that's going to end well.
Don't be fooled. They're only adorable until they swarm you and gnaw your face off.
Lately the plains have been even more bitterly cold than usual. Find out what's causing this weather before it starts costing lives.
Elementals are plentiful in Frostfire Ridge. Goren love eating them, and whatever the goren eat, they inherit its powers. Not good.
The Bloodmaul ogres have begun raiding Horde outposts, costing us soldiers and supplies. We believe a new warlord is to blame.
It's time to chop down a few ancient trees. Only the ones that are demonically corrupted, mind you. The rest, you can hug if you like.
Shadowmoon forces have abducted a Wildhammer shaman near the Cursed Woods. Rescue our foolhardy ally and bring the orcs to justice.
We have reports of the Shadowmoon prowling Gloomshade Grove, shrouding the land in foul magic. Disrupt their dark rituals at any cost.
Thunderlord hunting parties have been sighted to the north. Set an ambush in the cliffs and show them what the real Horde is made of!
The Shadow Council has wormed its way into a network of caves west of the garrison. We cannot allow it to gain a foothold in the region!
Killing full-grown rylaks has not diminished their numbers in the least. Scour their nesting grounds and end this menace at the source.
A strange disease is spreading among Gorgrond's ancients, driving them mad. Destroy them before the infection escalates.
Scouts have recovered a map of Blackrock supply caches hidden across Gorgrond. Destroying them would strike a grave blow to our enemy.
The Gorgrond genesaur have overhunted in their territory and are raiding nearby draenei camps for food. Attack them and lure them away.
A group of goren has settled in a valuable quarry nearby. We need to get them out if we plan to use the quarry in the future.
Gronnlings continue to interrupt our efforts to expand into Gorgrond. We need to thin their numbers if we wish to gain a foothold.
Iron Horde siege weapons are deadly at a distance but vulnerable up close. Targeting their armaments with a small force may prove wise.
Shivan have been sighted on the outskirts of Talador. They may be the first wave of a Burning Legion incursion. Investigation is warranted.
A cavern beneath an inhabited section of Talador has become unstable due to the appetite of the goren inside. We must protect those above.
A charismatic high arakkoa priest is inciting his congregation to raid nearby settlements in the name of Terokk. We must defend our allies.
Absolute power corrupts, and that's absolutely the reason we must neutralize this powerful warlock. Terminate with extreme prejudice.
From Azeroth to Draenor, bullies and their cronies remain the same. Please show our new "friends" how we deal with their kind on Azeroth.
The ogron are said to be violence incarnate, but I've heard your allies are called the same. Let's find out who lives up to their hype.
Shattered Hand orcs embrace pain, for they say it strengthens them. Make them very strong. Then very dead.
The Pale are twisted, cowardly wretches, but even scavengers can be deadly in sufficient numbers. Still, that's easily solved, isn't it?
Ravagers reproduce quickly and eat anything. Like crickets. They're also homicidal and roughly the size of horses. Not like crickets.
Our livestock have gone missing. Tracks point to the rylaks. Deal with the threat, but don't take them lightly.
A vicious wind serpent appears to be acting on orders from an unseen master, wearing down our defenses. Seek out and end this threat.
Our informants in the Shattered Hand have turned out to be double agents. Set up a covert meeting and eliminate them.
Energy-siphoning water spirits are giving our spellcasters fits. Time to bring in reinforcements.
The cause of our recent communal lethargy has been traced to Highmaul sorcerers. Find them and put an end to their sinister arcane rites.
Warsong shaman have enacted a spell to open an abyss beneath our feet! Kill all of them before the sands in the hourglass run out!
High ogre warriors are in battle array, screaming that they're going to "destroy the interlopers." Do you think they're talking about us?
Burning Blade orcs are attacking treasure hunters at Oshu'gun and looting their crystals. Could they be preparing for some dark ritual?
Our scouts have vanished without a trace! They were last seen entering gronn lands. Find out what happened to them.
Shadowmoon Valley is haunted by orc spirits that lash out in confusion and rage. Until they are put to rest, no one is safe.
The Thunderlord orcs are growing bold: their scouts follow Horde parties with little stealth or fear. Such arrogance deserves a response.
Wayward podlings have stolen a crate of our giant growth elixirs. Recover the potions before the creatures consume them and run amok.
Blackrock messengers have been spotted crisscrossing the region. Any missives they are carrying could prove invaluable to our cause.
Ogre slavers are carrying off our allies to fight in their arenas. Pose as a would-be gladiator and free the unwilling combatants.
We know the ogron are going to attack soon because they told us. No one ever said they were smart. Stop them before they do any real harm.
Redistributing wealth from the departed isn't stealing. Trouble is, there's a mighty arakkoan sorcerer who doesn't know it. Do let him know.
The Iron Horde's shredders are laying waste to Talador's forests. Bastards. If someone's doing that, it should be our forces.
The arakkoa have begun stealing and hoarding gold. Time to steal it back.
Saberon have begun attacking with wild abandon. They believe they have nine lives. Prove them wrong.
Our soldiers in the field need medical supplies, but Warsong orcs are patrolling the road. Escort the caravan so it makes its destination.
Warsong orcs have razed our camp to the north, and the lone survivor says they're headed this way. We must repel the invaders!
Hippos are taking over the Verdant Mire. They're violently territorial and extremely tough. They're also blocking key resources.
In this harsh environment, sturdy transportation is essential. Cripple the Iron Horde by taking out its greatest beasts of burden.
A noxious mist is pervading Blademoon Bloom. Find and neutralize the source so that our forces can pass safely through the region.
The pale have stolen a shipment of Iron Horde weaponry. Recover the armaments - by force if necessary - before our enemy does.
Habitat changes in Gorgrond have forced hydras to encroach on draenei settlements. It is a pity, but we must kill these desperate beasts.
Every year, great herds of clefthoof migrate through Gorgrond, causing tremors and dust storms. We must divert them from our camp.
Elementals are chaotic by nature and are best avoided. This elemental has something we need: resources. Make it an offer it cannot refuse.
Our garrison requires resources, so it's harvest time. Kindly remind this savage plant and its minions why we're atop the food chain.
An ancient has begun attacking everyone and everything in its path. On a related note, we're currently low on firewood.
We think the recent dread raven attacks are connected to the arakkoa. We'll investigate them. You hunt down and kill their minions.
War has ravaged the region's plant life, and the clefthoof don't have enough to eat. We should thin out their numbers before they starve.
Enraged, Stonegar has begun attacking shaman near the Throne of the Elements. We must send forces to aid.
Our former courier got spooked and dropped an important package from Karabor in a thicket of botani and ancients.  Retrieve the package!
Bladespire ogres have captured a band of laborers from the garrison. Infiltrate their fortress and free the workers.
Several gronn and ogron came here to attack us, but the dumb beasts are just fighting each other. Let's kill them all and end this farce.
Blackrock orcs are testing out their war machines on the region's unsuspecting fauna. This aggression will not stand!
Demons have been skulking about the Court of Souls, and it's not because they enjoy the scenery. Find out what they're plotting.
Agents of the Burning Legion are hunting down refugee draenei from Shattrath. Gather the refugees and take them to safety.
Several laborers have gone missing, and we fear that the arakkoa plan to burn them alive in sacrifice. We must save them!
We have intel that a unit of Shattered Hand orcs is en route to assist the Iron Horde in Talador. Too bad they'll never make it.
To the south lies Shadowfall Canyon, where wretched creatures are subjucating spirits of Fire, Earth, and Wind. Hopefully, no worse.
High ogres are enslaving gronn with pernicious magic, almost doubling the size of their army. We must put an end to the spellcasting.
Shadowmoon orcs are summoning void beasts through hastily opened portals that could tear Draenor apart, once again. Stop them!
Gronn attacked an alchemist's wagon, and now they're hopped up on strength elixirs.  Let's get 'em before they find the invisibility potions.
The genesaur and their botani minions are attacking caravans on the road to Talador. We'll make them rue the day they were sprouted!
Our scouts spotted a group of ogre slavers gathering in Gorgrond. We cannot allow them a chance to fortify their position. Attack!
Shattered Hand raiders do not simply kill, they take trophies from their victims. We know their next target. Stop them.
Arakkoa flocks are looting abandoned draenei homesteads. They're also killing any who try to stop them. That makes them our problem now.
The distressed spirits of fallen Azeroth soldiers have begun to rise. Quickly, let us end their torment.
Some sadistic saberon think the chaos on Draenor means they can butcher innocents without fear of punishment. Disabuse them of that notion.
Some important Burning Blade orcs wish to discuss battle strategy with Iron Horde leaders. It would be a shame if they never arrived.
A group of defectors wishes to escape the Iron Horde! Let's clear the way for them.
Modern anthropologists had hoped Draenor would reveal the origin of the rock flayer.  They were disappointed.
Scouts have heard rumors of valuables within a mysterious cave in the Umbrafen.
Rumors grow of a Pale orc that thrives on ambushing the unsuspecting for anything that shines.  He might be found in a cave to the southwest.
The Grimfrost ogres regularly rob Frostwolf orcs and offer them as sacrifices to Brorrok the Devourer.  Let's relieve them of their stolen goods.
Legends speak of a cave above the Nightmarsh replete with valuable trade resources - along with an amphibious abomination residing in it.
The frostwing screechers of the Southwind Cliffs are overpopulated.  If ignored, this will eventually disrupt mining operations.
We'll need to regularly fend off warpstalkers in the Shimmering Mor to ensure a steady supply of fey dragons for transport purposes.
The elementals of Gorgrond are regularly whipped into a frenzy by Dessicus of the Dead Pools.  Let's see what we can do about that.
The saberon continue to be a menace to our outpost in Gorgrond.  Let's show them why this world isn't named Sabronia.
Iron Horde artillery units have positioned themselves on the ridge above the Shivering Trench.  This is a clear and present danger!
Some say the podlings of Gloomshade Grove bow to the mad king of the east.  Find him, and end his reign of podling terror.
A reduced kaliri population would be greatly appreciated by virtually every hero moving about the skies, for all time.
Scouting reports indicate some substandard adventurers are trapped in Deathweb Hollow.  I suppose we should lend a hand.
The arakkoa have enslaved more outcasts and have resumed their excavation efforts.  Another setback for them is in order.
Kill the orcs in the mountains.
Kill the orcs in the mountains.
Don't you worry.  Just make like a bear, get in, get the honey, and get out.
The Shattered Hand clan is positioned on the Shattered Rise and likely to strike again.  Handle it!
The Highmaul ogres have an excavation underway at Stonecrag Gorge.  Get in there and extract information about their relics!
Lug'dol and his nascent brawler thugs are using our supply escorts for combat practice.  You know we can't allow this to continue.
The Iron Horde have built a harbor in Gorgrond that they call the Iron Docks. Show our enemy how fragile their vaunted "iron" truly is.
A little bird informed me that the arakkoa of Skyreach have been preying on our forward scouts. Make sure they regret that decision.
Orcs from an alternate universe invaded our Blackrock Mountain. How ironic. Let's educate them on what happened to the previous residents.
Using a mausoleum as a staging ground is a completely new level of disrespect. Let's allow the departed to rest with smiles on their faces.
The Bloodmaul use slave labor to fuel their efforts. If we liberate the miners, we'll disrupt their operations. Textbook win-win situation.
Two words: Orcish engineering.  Even odds their rail system will take care of itself, but let's stack the odds in our favor.
The Ziggy Sawdust X3-9 is the latest in clear-cutting technology. Unleash the adorable robot on the Everbloom and enjoy the show.
How convenient of Ner'zhul and his lackeys to flee into their clan's burial grounds. It will make choosing their graves much quicker.
Our enemies boast that their massive ship at the Iron Docks cannot be sunk. This crate of shiny new seaforium charges begs to differ.
The dread ravens are gathering scraps from below Skyreach. They are building more of those constructs or nests. They must be stopped.
The druids fear that the proto-drake populations are plummeting. Rescue their eggs from Warlord Zaela's army in Upper Blackrock Spire.
Scouts report that strange figures are lurking near Auchindoun, disturbing the mausoleums. We must destroy anything with even a hint of fel.
Rescuing slaves in the Bloodmaul Slag Mines is our priority, but to do this, we must thin the number of fire furies there.
Goblin engineers are designing weapons for Blackrock and Thunderlord orcs. Well, we have weapons too. Go to Grimrail Depot and use them.
Some magi stopped to smell the roses in the Everbloom. Oops. If we hurry, we should be able to save some of them.
Some of the Shadowmoon clan's treasures are poorly guarded. We'll take what we can and destroy the rest!
They won't stand it. They'll know we planned it. The Iron Horde will think we're a mirage, but it's just sabotage.
Atop Skyreach, the high arakkoa are building mechanical constructs as weapons of war. Stop them, but beware their dread raven guards.
To siege the Iron Horde held Blackrock Spire, we must rid it of dragonkin and proto-dragons. Their mysterious keeper must also perish.
The Shadow Council is raising warriors interred at Auchindoun to create draenei constructs. Stop them before they defile the place further.
The Bloodmaul have discovered a powerful artifact, and their warlord is overseeing the excavation. Ambush the warlord and take the artifact.
The Grimrail Depot owes its efficiency to goblin and orc overseers. Kill them, and you'll kill its ability to ship arms to distant camps.
We dispatched a mage to deal with a hostile pack of genesaur, but now he's on their side. He must be infected. Time to send in the cavalry.
Testing mission complete and all that.
The bloodmaul ogres of the Stonefury Cliffs are infamous as brutal slavemasters.  Show no quarter and free their slaves.
If our troops are to become battle hardened, there would be no better test than the immense magnaron, Drov the Ruiner.
The Sargerei have taken control of Socrethar's Rise and are establishing countless demonic portals, we can't let this continue.
We need to shut down the legion gateways in operation within Shattrath.  Strike out at their vigilant watchful eyes.
The Iron Horde is running critical supply missions from the beach of Ironfist Harbor.  Three of our best should disrupt their operations.
The Shattered Hand clan has established the ironically named Bladefist Hold.  Let's make a mockery of it.
With great risk comes great reward.  Plumb the dangers of Darksting Cave in southern Gorgrond and see what you can find.
The Steamscar of Gorgrond are notorious looters.  Let's repossess the valuables for great justice.
Shadow Council pillagers continue to ravage the Auchenai catacombs of the Tomb of Lights.
As it happens, the reagents used by the Shadow Council fetch a handy sum on the black market.  We're certain there's a stockpile in Gul'rok.
The goblins of Pinchwhistle *are* the noxious local environment.  I see no reason we shouldn't relieve them of some valuables.
Get it!
The wolfmother Gar'lua raises the most ferocious of Warsong wolves.  Their pelts would dent the Warsong war effort and fetch a tidy sum.
Even an ogre as incompetent as Ug'lok the Frozen can amass a fortune via slave labor, but be prepared to counter his magic should it happen to work.
Rumor has it that Brambleking Fili's staff points the way to a hidden cache.  Myth?
The Iron Horde excavations taking place in The Pit occasionally turn up rare diamonds.  Retrieve one and we'll make use of it.
Not only does the ammunition of the Iron Horde carry value on the black market, but lifting some means less for the Earthbreaker cannon.
You and I both know the arakkoa are loaded.  Feels like we could make a fortune just chipping away at the walls.
A joint operation between the Venture Co. and Iron Horde is taking place on Darktide Roost.  Profit must be some sort of motive.
The Iron Docks have resumed operations despite our previous incursions. Let us show them how base their iron is against our mettle.
The denizens of Skyreach have stymied the war effort in arakkoan territory. Time to implement our new strategy: Operation Open Season.
The Iron Horde and its lackeys have "energetically" refused to vacate our own Blackrock Mountain. Go collect back rent from their corpses.
The Sargerei and their allies continue their desecration of Auchindoun. I recommend executing our "no traitor left behind alive" policy.
Ogres are bringing in slaves to shore up defenses in the mines. Free the slaves, and the area will be vulnerable to attack.
The Blackrocks need an uninterrupted supply of metal to fuel production of their war machines. Let's make life difficult for them.
The natives are restless. Again. The Kirin Tor have asked us to help them with some "gardening."
Our shaman have prepared a ritual to return souls summoned by the Shadowmoon to rest. Go and perform this ritual at the burial grounds.
The Iron Horde's flagship is at the Iron Docks. It's intimidating, but if it's steered into a shoal, it'll founder like any other boat.

Name_lang: Is It a Bird? A Zeppelin?
Description_lang: Apexis devices are sun powered, but what if the sun is blocked? Zeppelins will work, and the goblins might help. Go, but pack airsick bags.
A fortress in a volcano is both ingenious and foolhardy. Impenetrable, yes, but a shaman can cause an eruption that will decimate it.
Soulbinder Nyami has hidden caches of reagents for the Sargerei's summoning rituals all across Auchindoun. Find the caches and destroy them.
A mineshaft has collapsed, and those Bloodmaul dogs have left the enslaved miners down there to die. We must dig them out!
A train full of artillery and explosives is about to leave the depot. Detonating one bomb should be enough to destroy the entire payload.
The river we've been using as our water source has been tainted by those nasty spores! Find a new source before people get thirsty.
The spirits of the burial grounds are restless. Seek their knowledge and their power to end Ner'zhul's scheming once and for all.
With some diving gear and a little luck, a seaborne attack could be our best chance of infiltrating the heavily fortified Iron Docks.
The arakkoa view us "ground dwellers" as nothing more than beasts. Let us see what they think after we lay waste to their lofty spires.
Getting into Blackrock Spire will not be easy, but we have a secret weapon: mole machines. The Black Irons will never know what hit them.
A portal in Auchindoun links Draenor to the demon world of Argus. Cut off the Legion's reinforcements: destroy every trace of the portal.
Slaves in the Slag Mines are ripe for revolt. Aid them. Then ask if they've dug up any powerful relics lately. Try to be subtle.
Trains symbolize inevitability, but you've never put much stock in fate. That's good: you've got a huge infrastructure to shatter.
The Kirin Tor who were sent to Gorgrond have gone silent. Turned or slain? Find out what's going on, and get them back on task if you can.
The time for a critical assault on Highmaul is at hand.  To victory!
The time for a critical assault on Highmaul is at hand.  To victory!

The time for a critical assault on Highmaul is at hand.  To victory!
Rumored not to exist, yet clearly baseless.
The Netherstorm must have come from somewhere.  Get on a boat, sail northeast, and bring something good back while you're at it.
Some shifty troll sold our troops a bunch of worthless junk.  Rough him up a bit and get a refund!
The Warsong clan stationed in Lok-rath is rumored to stockpile some strange form of currency.  It may hold some historic significance.
It's best not to lose a bet with the janitor.
Mogor the Ogre is having trouble with some gladiators, but slaughtering other ogres would look bad for him.  He'll pay us for the dirty work.
The ruthless war prides of the Bloodmane have made off with the Reveries of Sethek, scrolls sacred to the outcasts.
The once-great city of Shattrath continues to be subjugated by the legion.  Cry havoc, and let slip the followers of war.
Sometimes, a follower's skills just aren't cutting the mustard.  The ring offers a rare opportunity to retrain.
Slay our Alliance adversaries for the glory of the Horde!  Go forth to victory!
Slay our Alliance adversaries for the glory of the Horde!  Go forth to victory!
Slay our Alliance adversaries for the glory of the Horde!  Go forth to victory!
Slay our Alliance adversaries for the glory of the Horde!  Go forth to victory!

Slay our Horde adversaries for great justice and for the Alliance!

Slay our Alliance adversaries for the glory of the Horde!  Go forth to victory!
Gorgrond plays host to one of the most fearsome creatures in all Draenor.  Tremble before his might, but come back with some plunder afterwards.
A manifestation of a Sun God, Rukhmar demands fealty and obedience.  She will not be defeated easily.
If you really want to join the Steamwheedle Preservation Society, you've got to really care about Highmaul artifacts.
While we were occupied with the sabotage of the Dark Portal, Blingtron managed to build a vault of riches.  Find it!
We could use a master tactician around here.  Plus, we might get some autographs.
We could use a master tactician around here.  Plus, we might get some autographs.
Rumor has it there's a chili cook-off soon, and frankly I'm tired of eating the same gruel every day.  Send someone to get whatever wins.
Behold!  Endless customization awaits in this system within a system within a system.
Coldtusk the boar continues to roam the shivering trench, and clearly we can't rely on the ravagers to take care of him.
The furies that roam the Southwind Cliffs have been known to leave their dead frozen in place.  Perhaps there are things worth retrieving.
The marshes of the Umbrafen are the stomping ground of Ba'ruun, a danger to all that need enter the fen.
Rumors speak of a ghostly talbuk that haunts the southern reaches of Shadowmoon Valley, we should investigate.
Comb the northern wastelands of Gorgond for Rolkor.  Find him and defeat him for the glory of the garrison.
Our scouts speak of a cavern in northern Gorgrond in which a strange ogron named Gelgor of the Blue Flame lies.
Hen-Mother Hami.  She who breeds the swooping terrors of the sky.  Find her, subdue her, and restore freedom to the skies.
The Iron Horde have equipped a particularly violent elekk named Steeltusk.  Let's make sure this doesn't become more common.
Scouts report a many-headed beast named Festerbloom waylaying travelers crossing the Murkbog.  Clear the path for everyone's sake.
Rumors swirl of an ancient gone awry in the undergrowth.  Track down this "Shadowbark" and take care of business.
We've isolated the murderous Warmaster Blugthol to a tower within Mar'gok's Overwatch.  It's time to take him out.
Just north of Grommashar dwell the Sabermaw clan, notorious outpost raiders.  Strike out at their leader, Soulfang, and crush their morale.
A very large Iron Horde fuel-storage tank sits alongside a rail bridge to the north. Crack the tank open, add some dynamite.  BOOM!
We suspect a goblin merchant of selling to both us and the Iron Horde. Tail him, and if he is double-dealing, drag him back by his ears.
Iron Horde raiders have descended on nearby draenei villages. Find the raiders' camp and raid it. Turnabout, they say, is fair play.
Word has it that an Iron Horde mine near our outpost has hit a rich vein. We can't let them have nice things. Storm in and claim the mine.
Iron Horde cuisine is revolting, but the refugees need food. Find orc camps and pilfer what rations they have. Mints might be prudent too.
Rumor has it that the Thunderlord clan is using strange "blades of omen" that can change size. Destroy these weapons while we can.
Grommash has a legendary ego and temper. Hit the Warsong hard and he'll be consumed with the need for vengeance. We want him distracted.
Blackrock scouts have discovered a vast trove of metal ore perfect for making weapons. Make sure they never report their findings.
Curiously, our scouts say a Shadowmoon encampment is always vulnerable at night. You'd think they'd be more used to the dark. Oh well.
Some Shattered Hand raiders have scattered, but though they look haggard, they may soon find new victims to splatter.
Those Highmaul ogres are annexing more land than we can afford to lose. We're green-lighting a terminal solution to this problem: you.
Bloodmaul ogres enslave others and then rely on their forced labor. Go inspire the downtrodden by kicking the fight out of their oppressors.
The Bladespire clan has concocted a "foolproof" plan of defense. Make it backfire by killing their elite and leaving their "fools" alive.
We cannot allow the arakkoa to acquire more of their deadly Apexis technology. Raid their excavation sites. Leave nothing but dust behind!
Our alchemists have found uses for the oils secreted by arakkoa feathers. Gather as many as you can - by any means necessary.
We have crafted a device to mimic an arakkoa's cries for help. Deploy it in the Spires of Arak to draw our feathery foes into an ambush.
The podlings have been raiding the graves of our allies to feed one of their genesaur. Recover the bodies. If they want mulch, mulch them!
We need to get the gronn riled again. Kill the local meat-based wildlife and see if starvation turns them against the Iron Horde nearby.
Our scouts report that the botani are snatching workers from the quarries. Kill the primals and find out what they are using the orcs for.
The reckless warlock Gul'dan intends to create a fel volcano in the center of Shadowmoon Valley. Stop him before he dooms us all.
Shadow Council agents plan to cut a path through Tanaan and pave it with their enemies' bones. Such an atrocity must not come to pass.
Warlocks in the northwest are draining life from the land, preparing to summon a demon lord. Well? Don't just stand there!
Pale orcs stole a powerful trinket and fled to the mountains. Now they vow to kill anyone who comes near "the precious." Challenge accepted!
Massive flooding has cut off our supply lines, and the water elementals responsible show no signs of stopping. Let's hang them out to dry.
A doomsday weapon has been enchanted to look like an adorable baby clefthoof. Clefthoof violently defend their young. Proceed with caution.
Disrupt tense negotiations between the Iron Horde and the Highmaul ogres to acquire an Abrogator Stone for Khadgar.
A powerful Bloodmaul magma-shaper is using an Abrogator Stone as a piece of navel jewelry. Don't tell Khadgar where we got it.
A failed Stonemaul assault on the Overlook Ruins has left ogre corpses everywhere. Search them for an Abrogator stone!
Ogres are wagering an Abrogator Stone on an upcoming Ring of Blood gladiatorial contest. Send in the ringers.
Scouts have discovered a ruined ogre guard tower in Talador. It's haunted. Also, we're running out of scouts.
Good news! We've located some Elemental Runes that Khadgar is looking for. Bad News: They're in The Pits.
The Iron Horde is moving an Elemental Rune via train to the Blackrock Foundry. It's ambush time.
In the chaos of the battle of Shattrath, the Sargerei absconded with some of the Elemental Runes that Khadgar is looking for.
The Iron Horde have subjugated a stone fury in Ironfist Harbor. It's got the Elemental Runes Khadgar seeks.
The Bladefist clan are capturing pale prisoners. We suspect they're looking for the same Elemental Runes as Khadgar.
Elemental Runes have been smuggled into the Iron Siegeworks. Essentially a suicide mission. Send followers you don't like.
Amethon has been long forgotten, deep in a cave in Talador. His crystals are very valuable.
Gor'thul, betrayer of the Shattered Hand, is an outcast. It is said he has befriended a lot of cats.
Nullifier Darkoor has been in hiding long enough. It's time to take him down and put an end to the Fel Breakers once and for all.
Undertow appears from the depths, pulling boats into the sea and destroying our lines of contact between Tanaan Jungle and Shadowmoon Valley.
A massive rockworm has taken residence on the shores of Gorgrond, devouring the local lobstroks.
Hemet Nesingwary would be very interested in his head.
PH
Reforge the weapon of the most brutal gladiator to fight in the Ring of Blood.
Claim the power of the arakkoa god before the Adherents of Rukhmar can take it for themselves.

Name_lang: Relic Hunter: Grimoire of Nameless Void
Description_lang: Destroy the ancient barrier to access this dark and powerful tome.
Seek the blessings of Frostfire to empower the ancient Thunderlord spear.
Take the cursed skull mask from the legendary Laughing Skull assassin.
Recover the ancient crystal shards to restore this mysterious artifact of the draenei.
A strike against the Foundry could cripple the war machinery of the Iron Horde. Our forces await your command.
A strike against the Foundry could cripple the war machinery of the Iron Horde. Our forces await your command.

The more slaves we free at the Stonefury Cliffs, the more we weaken the Bloodmaul.
Scouts report that a rapid assault on Socrethar's Rise could turn up an additional stash of apexis crystals.

A rare lily grows in the waters of Talador.  Our alchemists say it is many times more efficient than frostweed.
A disgruntled Bladespire Chef has provided us with a lead on an ancient map hidden in the mines beneath the citadel.
A disgruntled Bladespire Chef has provided us with a lead on an ancient map hidden in the mines beneath the citadel.
A Steamscar saberon has been caught skulking around our walls. If we let him go, he's agreed to sell out a rival shaman who has been mapping the location of many hidden treasures.
A farmer claims knowledge of where many of Talador's secrets are hidden, and will share them if we'll help destroy the demons that ruined his land.
Rumors are swirling that a raid on an Outcast hovel has yielded a particularly interesting map. Intercept the arakkoa before they return to Skyreach!
A Warsong elder carrying historical documents important to the clan is communing at the Elemental Plateau. Relieve her of her burdens.
Ancient carvings in the tombs of the Fortress of Anguish may lead us to discover many secrets in Shadowmoon Valley. We'll have to fight our way in.
Ancient carvings in the tombs of the Fortress of Anguish may lead us to discover many secrets in Shadowmoon Valley. We'll have to fight our way in.
The Umbrafen swamps have been overgrown by giant fungi for as long as anyone can remember - why are Ogre ruins buried here?
The Shadowmoon Clan have interred their dead in this area for generations - find out more about their history.
The Thunderlord regard Colossal's Fall as a sacred location, claiming it was their clan who felled this Colossal many decades ago.
Relics of long-forgotten orc clans can be found by carefully traversing between the Daggermaw Flows lava streams - and dealing with deadly fire elementals.
The Iron Horde are attempting to unearth long-lost ogre artifacts in the Broken Spine area. Evict them and claim the rewards as your own.
The botani have claimed the abandoned ogre fortress at the Overlook Ruins as a new incubator. Stop them before they overgrow all of Gorgrond.

Name_lang: We Will Fight In the Shadar
Description_lang: The outcast arakkoa were forced to abandon much of their written knowledge and history when the high arakkoa attacked Veil Shadar.
The ghosts of ogre sorcerers haunt the Ango'rosh ruins, guarding artifacts forgotten by all others.
The high arakkoa have enslaved their outcast brethren to dig in the apexis excavation site, looking for ancient artifacts. Set the workers free.
Many shiny trinkets and precious valuables have been lost in Sethekk Hollow, the place where cursed arakkoa are cast out from Skyreach.

The Steamwheedle Preservation Society management needs the Stonecrag dig site to be an ogre-free zone before their workers will agree to excavate, and have promised a cut of the proceeds if we help out.
We've heard reports that the Steamwheedle Preservation Society is looking to start a dig site at the razed Warsong outpost - why wait for them when you can claim the easy finds now?
The ancient communal site of Oshu'gun holds offerings from various orc clans. If not for the murderous void elementals unleashed by the pale, it would be a nice place to visit.
A monstrous beast roams the Murkbog.  Our alchemists say they can harvest it for a bounty of alchemy supplies.
Scavengers gnaw and pick at the fallen.  Kill them so we can do some scavenging of our own.
Blacksmiths know that furies can be harvested for the best flux.  Snuff the fires and bring it home.
The Shadowmoon clan possess weaponry we can harness for raw magic.  Raid their encampment and collect their enchanted weapons.
Ogre are known to possess massive, thick, and long swords.  Disenchanting them makes a tremendous amount of dust.
Our engineers are excited about tearing apart a siege engine for parts.  Let's take one down and let them have their fun.
The pale are expert scavengers.  Let's relieve them of some of that salvage.
The arakkoa decorate their weapons and armor with fantastic jewels.  Acquire them and let our jewelcrafters cut them into something useful.
Apparently the goren can't digest the valuable gems they eat.  Your mission should be clear.
If we can decipher some stolen iron horde documents, we can find and assassinate their scouts.
It's time to make some changes to the Iron Horde's orders.  If we can kill the guards, we can rewrite history before it happens.
There's some rather large clefthoof in Nagrand.  Let's take one down before they are killed by trappers.
Iron Horde tents are made from rugged leather that can be crafted into fine leather armor.
Rylak's collect an immense amount of fur when building their nests.  Raid a nest and recover the fur.
The garn are primarily known for their ferocity, but they are only slightly lesser well known for their sumptuous furry pelts.
Our need for equipment upgrades never ends, take a few of our best to the apexis excavation site.
We'll leave the elementals of Nagrand to themselves right after we've gotten some of the elemental samples we need.
Head to neutral ground at the Ring of Trials and learn a thing or two about fighting alongside ogres.
As we have a number of arakkoa allies, let's run some joint operations to build relations.
With the installation of a negatronic control unit, a true emotional bond between lifeform and machine can happen!  Get one!
The saberon have highly developed rituals and customs.  Live among them, learn their ways, and gain strength from this experience.
We need someone to document the devastation taking place here on Draenor. Head to Nagrand and photograph all you can.
Your photos turned out great, but now we need some more creative shots. Head back out to the field and see what you can do!
You will find Yozshura the Blademaster atop Mount Volwrath.  Seek his wisdom, challenge him, and return enlightened.
The troops are hungry, go pick up a few pies.
An Iron Horde submarine is making a break for our shipyard.  Take it out.
kill stuff
We need to find more paladin allies if we are to have any hope of bringing the fight to the Legion.
There have been sightings of Legion scouts in the skies above the forest canopy.
An ancient scroll in our archives describes a Titan communicator somewhere in Val'Sharah that could provide us with invaluable knowledge.

The Horde have set up a blockade around their garrison.  Break through and you can raid the Horde navy.
Assault the Iron Horde defense in the Barrier Sea to unlock access to the waters around Tanaan.  Success grants access to Hellfire Citadel naval missions.
The Alliance have set up a blockade around their garrison.  Break through to raid and plunder.
Push the Iron Horde out of the South Seas by defeating their blockade.  Success grants access to the primal resources around Nagrand.

Name_lang: The Second Time is the Charm
Description_lang: Now that our ships are more equipped, re-engage the enemy.  It's lurking in the same area.

Name_lang: The Second Time is the Charm
Description_lang: Now that our ships are more equipped, re-engage the enemy.  It's lurking in the same area.
You've never lived until you've taken down an enemy vessel while you're both flirting with watery disaster.
These destroyers plan to shell a Laughing Skull village near the Iron Docks. It's our closest foothold against the Iron Horde. We can't lose it.
We designed submarines specifically to sneak up on unsuspecting carriers.  We've set up a carrier in the reef for you to practice.
We've set up submarines at different depths in Frostfire Bay.  Take a destroyer out and train them in the art of sub hunting.
Although goren infest the Molten Quarry, iron ore is plentiful there. So are Alliance scum. Don't let that destroyer secure their grip on the area.
Demons and Shadow Council agents have overrun much of Shattrath. Even so, we will keep fighting. We shall not yield while the Alliance still stands.
We've heard rumors of a powerful new demon presence in Faronaar. We should investigate before it threatens our hold on the area.
There is a powerful beacon of the Light somewhere in Azsuna. We should find it.
Senegos' prime consort has sent out a cry for help. We owe it to our allies to send aid.
Iron Horde forces have been harvesting potent toxins in the Writhing Mire and using them in combat. Now they're shipping a batch of toxins north.
This sub just limped back home for repairs, only to find the harbor nearly deserted. Finish off the sub while we keep the enemy busy elsewhere.
These two vessels are heading south in a hurricane. Even Hellscream wouldn't have sent them out unless their mission was dire. We must intercept them.
Rumor has it a cargo fleet recently sank out here, far from land. Unfortunately we're not the only ones who've heard this rumor.
Surely these vessels are just ferrying bird enthusiasts to the bay. Not beast tamers who plan to enslave its massive hydras for the Iron Horde. Surely.
The Iron Horde uses subs to transport gold up and down the western coast. Taking one out would hit Hellscream's pocket and fill our coffers.
This enemy sub is loaded with gold, so it can't outrun us. Instead, it's been hiding out between a rocky shoal and a whirlpool, hoping to lure us to our doom.
A damaged engine has crippled a destroyer far from shore. That's what happens when you only value warriors and plunder. Not that the gold should go waste.
While mutineers were seizing this destroyer, storms broke out, and a whirlpool ensnared the ship. That's bad luck. And thanks to us, it's about to get worse.
In this poor weather, Hellscream has sent subs to harry our fleet. Act decisively so that they never again see the light of day.
Enemy destroyers are terrorizing the waters west of the Spires of Arak. Crushing them won't restore the lives that've been lost, but it'd be a good start.
With no wind and a ripped mainsail, an enemy carrier has slowed to a crawl, along with its escorts. Make sure their troops and cargo never make landfall.
Enemy subs have taken a sudden interest in this area. They may be tracking down an elemental rune. In the wrong hands, it could prove devastating.
Storms have broken out around the Ancestral Grounds. The enemy vessel off the coast may be to blame. Also the fact that most shaman loathe the Iron Horde.
Evidently Hellscream thought subs might be a safer way to transport elemental runes. Safer, yes. Sneaky, no.
Hellscream should realize by now that the elements won't willingly serve the Iron Horde. And trying to compel their obedience is unwise.
Lately the Iron Horde has been gathering magical items. They've learned brute force can't solve everything. Remind them it still has its uses.
A shipment of abrogator stones is on its way to Grommashar. We must intercept it. The Iron Horde is trouble enough without a bunch of magical gems.
An enemy carrier has veered off course, and it's emanating powerful magic. Something odd is afoot. Find out what. More importantly, claim that magic.
Several magi and their schooner have been taken into the Iron Horde's "protection". Rescue the magi. Their gratitude could pay well.
Iron Horde vessels are often attacked by lobstrok here, and so Hellscream means to slay their matriarch. Coming to her aid would be in our best interests.
Northwest of Talador, offshore, is an unyielding rock vise called the Colossal's Fist. The Iron Horde hasn't yet discovered it. Arrange an introduction.
Captain Ironbeard is a deadly menace on the seas, but he's obsessed with a kraken that doesn't exist. Distract him and then launch a sneak attack.
Shattered Hand forces just dispatched these vessels, which headed straight into a storm. Their recklessness will work to our advantage.
Subtlety isn't really Hellscream's strong suit. Probably these ships thought the mountains would hide their approach.
So what if they're nowhere near Horde or Alliance waters? Sooner or later, they will be.
These ships were loaded with containers of raw fel before they left Ironhold Harbor. Wherever they're headed, we must destroy them and their deathly cargo.
The Iron Horde keeps sending fresh workers and supplies to the Dark Portal. Should we take pity and let their ships through so they can rebuild it? No.
These bastards have been playing tag with our forces, landing hits on our forces, only to evade our counterattacks. It's hurting our troops and their morale.
Kilrogg Deadeye has made his choice. Now his Bleeding Hollow orcs travel to Hellfire Citadel and return to Tanaan empowered by demonic blood.
Hellscream has posted a sub near the Horde's main base on Ashran. Take that sub out. Alliance, that means you, too. Factional hatreds have no place here.

Name_lang: If a Tree Falls in the Forest
Description_lang: Iron Horde forces have landed in Tangleheart, endangering its rich soil and plentiful timber. Also its powerful ancients. Who were already pretty angry.

Name_lang: A Ship in Harbor Is Safe, But...
Description_lang: These ships are about to leave Ironhold Harbor. They're probably still hung over from last-minute partying. They're certainly not expecting a fight.
An enemy carrier has seized control of the Darktide Strait. Losing that waterway would hurt Horde shipping concerns worldwide. Our course is clear.
A true warrior would only hunt a sub in bad weather. Barefoot. In arctic waters. Against the current. Both ways.
Outmanned thirty to one. Alliance weaklings would call this a risky fight. In the Horde, we call it a target-rich environment.
Battleship counters destroyer, but carrier counters battleship. Sub counters carrier, but destroyer counters sub. In short, luck will decide this fight.
The city of Elodor houses the draenei's leaders, who are allied with the Alliance. Teach both groups a lesson: seize one of their gold shipments.
The so-called dragons living here are fragile mounts, but foolish draenei pay well for them. Divert their latest cargo of gold to a better cause: ours.
When Alliance forces sailed to Shadowmoon, their ship arrived intact. Maybe draenei aren't as cursed as we thought. Maybe they even brought gold with them.
The mail armor in this vessel's cargo hold will serve us well once we spice it up a bit.
This vessel is taking a cargo full of leather armor to Alliance fighters in Zeth'Kur. Leather shouldn't be wasted on them. Isn't lace more their thing?
This Alliance carrier is heading for Stormshield with fresh troops and supplies. But it's a long journey between Shadowmoon Valley and Ashran.
Cowardly Alliance dogs have begun targeting our carriers even when they are far from Shadowmoon waters. Show them what a true threat looks like.
The waters around Shadowmoon Valley are regularly patrolled by Alliance subs, but these two are far from shore. They look lonely. Let's send them company.
If we steal Alliance-bound boots, and a barefoot Alliance mage trips and dies, would that count as a Horde victory? Why, yes. Plus, hey, new boots.
Horde vessels wanted for Alliance raid. Must love plunder and long walks on the beach. High tolerance for the colors blue and violet a plus.
Alliance forces in Shadowmoon have an easy life. Lush forests, mild weather, supply shipments... maybe even fresh bacon. Make those bastards pay.
The Earthen Ring kindly requests that all plundered mail armor be divided equally among those who wear it. Otherwise, the elements might become displeased.
A shipment of tailored goods from Shadowmoon Valley is headed for our enemies in Stormshield. Intercept it, and share in the spoils.
Draenei-crafted plate is just as sturdy as Horde-crafted plate. Tell your soldiers they will seize and wear this cargo, or they will go naked into battle.
Another day, another Alliance shipment to Ashran. Are they trying to be stealthy, heading so far east before circling back to Stormshield? Pathetic.
An enemy carrier guards the channel entrance. If we take it out, we can storm Scuttler's Coast to the north, and cut off Alliance shipments to the south.
With Archmage Khadgar elsewhere on business, an enemy vessel has secured the eastern passage into Zangarra. They expect a fight. Let's not disappoint them.
This vessel is carrying plenty of plate armor; Alliance soldiers just happen to be wearing it. Why are you letting Alliance scum wear your armor?
This destroyer looks to be disabled far from land. But our scouts report this is just an act: a submarine is circling in the waters below.
These radiant and perilous waters absorbed their magical properties from precious stones lining the sea floor. Such a gem would make a powerful necklace.
The name sounds peaceful, but your crew should bring gas masks. The atmosphere here tends to be toxic, which is doubtless why the Horde sent a sub.
Frostboar Point is tactically worthless; it hardly merits a carrier patrol. Somehow the Horde has discovered our plans to export the area's boars.
The orcs who named the Coldsnap Coast didn't mean that its weather was a temporary cold spell. They meant the cold would snap most people in two.
Bloodmaul ogres live here alongside their ogron masters, who constantly hammer the ground with boulders. All in all, it's a fun getaway spot.
Frostangler Bay is a virtual cornucopia of disgusting-looking marine life. But it's palatable enough if you cook it properly. Bring back a fat haul.
Horde forces plan to attack the Icescar Boneyard. If they fail, their deaths will only fuel the Shadow Council's foul sorcery. Stop the Horde, whatever it takes.
Several races on Draenor offer excellent pay for these giant mushrooms. That said, the shortsighted Horde will quickly wipe them out if we don't intervene.
Yes, it's constantly snowing here, but it also has volcanic activity. No, it's never a comfortable temperature. Look, you're not going ashore anyway.
This far north, Horde forces seem to think themselves safe from our ships. But then thinking never was their strong suit.
Battleship counters destroyer, but carrier counters battleship. Sub counters carrier, but destroyer counters sub. Thus, skill will be this fight's deciding factor.
Driven by bloodlust, orc animals target our carriers even when they're far from Frostfire waters. We won't meekly endure this aggression. Strike back.
Stop complaining. You never know: they might not smell that bad.
Our spies have noted regular supply shipments to Wor'gol via the Southwind Cliffs. The Horde hasn't noted our noting them. We've noted that, too.
These Horde vessels are rounding Highmaul on their way north. If ogres don't seize their cargo of plate armor, it will soon outfit our enemies. Stop them.
When Horde forces sailed to Frostfire, their ship arrived mostly intact. Perhaps orcs aren't witless brutes. Unless they left behind valuable cargo.
Pretend you're getting them from a big brother or sister. But give them a thorough scrubbing before you put them on. Just in case.
The orcs of Throm'var are supplying the Horde with fine furs and supple leather. Such a pity they'll be used to garb our boorish foes.
These battleships are so overburdened with cargo, their sailors hardly need to swab the decks. Teach them the value of caution, and lighten their load.
Hellscream's forces have recently grown scarce along the Orunai Coast. Now the Horde dares to use it as drop-off point for cargo.
Take out that enemy supply ship, but act quickly if anyone goes overboard. The orcs don't call it Frostbite Deep for nothing.
Procuring quality leather can be tedious, but the Horde plans to shell the hydras here and skin them. Exhausting work. Perfect setup for a lucrative win.
Shipments for Wor'gol must first pass through the Pale Cove's treacherous currents and jagged rocks. That will be the perfect time for us to strike.
Orcish cloth armor is just as soft and comfortable as ours. Tell your magi they will seize and wear this cargo. No exceptions, gnomes. Make it work.
A Horde warrior bound for Frostfire Ridge clumsily dropped a magic necklace overboard. Put him and his vessel out of their misery.
[ph]

Name_lang: It's a Boat, It's a Plane, It's... Just a Riverbeast.
Description_lang: The Iron Horde swooped in when they identified a rogue submarine closing in on their stronghold.  Unfortunately for them, it was just a riverbeast.
The deep waters of Draenor's oceans have seen many deaths and precious little peace. This ship and its crew are doomed to wander the seas for eternity.
This ghost ship lies in wait, attacking unwary sailors who approach the treacherous shoals off Gorgrond's eastern coast.
Seizing a fortune proved this destroyer's undoing. Its crew turned on each other, only to become cursed ghosts, unable to spend the gold they gave their lives for.
A young shark has been abandoned in a storm off the coast of Nagrand.  Defend it from the Iron Horde and it will likely follow you home.
Uncharted waters proved deadly to these sailors, who still roam the area as murderous ghosts. That said, they were well paid before their deaths.
On the one hand, great riches. On the other hand, furious walking corpses. Oh, come now. We all know what choice you're going to make.
Sabotaged by spies, these carriers sank on their way to battle. Denied a glorious death in battle, their ghostly crews sink other ships out of bitterness.
The hulls of destroyers are so thick, it's impossible to pierce it with normal ammunition.  We've crafted battleships with the sole purpose of penetrating destroyer armor.
Transport ships are required to deliver troops to battle or to load up valuable cargo.  Take a transport on this training mission and ensure it reaches its destination intact.
We designed submarines specifically to sneak up on unsuspecting carriers.  We've set up a carrier in the bay. See if you can sneak up on it.
The best way to take out battleships is by air.  Take a carrier out and have your ace bomber pilots put some holes into it.
[ph]
We've set up submarines at different depths off the coast of Shadowmoon Valley.  Take a destroyer out and train them in the art of sub hunting.
The hulls of destroyers are so thick, it's impossible to pierce it with normal ammunition.  We've crafted battleships with the sole purpose of penetrating destroyer armor.
The best way to take out battleships is by air.  Take a carrier out and have your ace bomber pilots put some holes into it.
[ph]
[ph]
Capture Ironfist Harbor and interrogate prisoners as to the whereabouts of Gul'dan's flagship.
Captured prisoners indicated that Gul'dan's flagship was last seen in this area of dangerous shoals.
Should give you a huge success chance boost, if it's the first mission of the day. Also should give you a cool item!
A Horde sub has been spotted spying around our base.  Take your new destroyer out and end it.
Our forward outpost has additional blueprints drafted up and a prototype ship.  Take the transport out and load up the shipment.
An Alliance sub has been spotted spying around our base.  Take your new destroyer out and end it.
Our forward outpost has additional blueprints drafted up and a prototype ship.  Take the transport out and load up the shipment.
[ph]
[ph]
Countless munitions are created in Blackrock Foundry, then infused with fel energies in Hellfire Citadel. It's vital that we intercept or destroy whatever we can.
Keeping the Iron Reaver in good repair is a full-time job, and it requires a steady supply of parts from Blackrock Foundry. Disrupt that supply.
Blackrock Foundry regularly ships newly forged cannons to Tanaan, where they bolster Hellfire Citadel's defenses. Every ship we sink saves thousands of lives.
There is someone out here who knows about the Pillars of Creation. We must find them.
We need the most fearless Illidari to join our cause if we are to have any chance of defeating the Legion.
A waterlogged crate has washed up on shore.  Break through the Iron Horde and pick it up.
If we can find a usable Legion gateway, we can launch an assault on one of their worlds and take it as our own.
Vhaka the Vile and her crew once terrorized Draenor's seas, killing and plundering without remorse. Cursed for their evil deeds, they lash out at the living.
Although his surprise attacks were legend, Giras the Guileful was just as infamous for his gambling addiction. Even now he's said to enjoy wagering on cards or dice.
Push the Iron Horde out of the South Seas by defeating their blockade.  Success grants access to the primal resources around Nagrand.
Assault the Iron Horde defense in the Barrier Sea to unlock access to the waters around Tanaan.  Success grants access to Hellfire Citadel naval missions.

Transport ships are required to deliver troops to battle or to load up valuable cargo.  Take a transport on this training mission and ensure it reaches its destination intact.

The sticky, sweet liquid inside of swamplighter hives is highly combustible. Extract some and we can use it as a crude oil substitute.
The white-hot cores of the abyssals assaulting Shattrath could be useful as a compressed fuel source, if we can obtain a few.
Poundface has cornered a small group of our allies bringing oil from the Blackrock Foundry. Help them get the oil back to our garrison.
An elder Warsong shaman's spirit has been disturbed by unrest in Nagrand. The ogres would be willing to trade some supplies with us if we can put it to rest.
Our allies in Spires of Arak have requested our aid against a large swarm of ravager wasps threatening their oil-pumping operations.
Deep within Auchindoun, Draenei power crystals still hum with life. We can surely use them as a source of fuel.
Two enormous watery monsters guard a strange oil-producing plant deep in the Everbloom. We should investigate.
Two powerful ogres have taken over a portion of the mines containing a shipment of valuable fuel.
Terrible void creatures are coming from a deep chasm in the burial grounds. There may be other valuables down there as well.
A master of beasts has been seen escorting a shipment of oil to Blackrock Mountain. Stop him!
A group of podlings has been spotted near some recently-formed tar pits in Gorgrond. If we defeat them, we can extract the fuel.
The corrupting blood in Spires of Arak has turned the carrion-consuming species into undead monstrosities.
A decrepit ogre caravan was spotted in Frostfire, surrounded by hostile wildlife. It looks like they were hauling oil.
The void's effect on Draenor has become more pronounced. Vile bloods of the land are emerging.
A powerful spider named Death's Bite has returned as an undead, and terrorizes Talador yet again.
A group of tiny fiery puppies was spotted deep within Blackrock Foundry. If we save them, we may be able to raise them.
Two enormous breakers have been spotted out on Gorgrond. What better way to test our might?
A group of burning blademaster spirits has been roused by the activities in Nagrand. We should investigate.
Some ancient artifacts containing untold knowledge are being jealously guarded by arakkoa out in Spires of Arak.
The ogres found a huge supply cache out in Frostfire Ridge. Who's up for some ogre hunting?
A group of frost furies has gathered in the snowy wastes of Frostfire Ridge and laid waste to a caravan carrying valuable weaponry.
Rumors abound of terrible demons near Shattrath that could drive a follower insane by just looking at them.
Tanaan Jungle is a harsh landscape, home to some of the most powerful beasts on this world.
A deep chasm, filled with blackness, was found deep within the burial grounds. Who knows what horrors await us there?
The botani of Shadowmoon have regrown, stonger than ever. Let us show them our might and test ourselves in the process.
A local privateer has offered their service attacking the Alliance around Shadowmoon.  All you have to do is smuggle some goods past the Iron Horde blockade in the South Sea.
A local privateer has offered their service attacking the Alliance around Shadowmoon.  All you have to do is smuggle some goods past the Iron Horde blockade in the South Sea.
A local privateer has offered their service attacking the Horde around Frostfire.  All you have to do is smuggle some goods past the Iron Horde blockade in the South Sea.

Captain Thokash found himself outgunned by a host of Alliance ships.  If you assist, he will deploy to the north to increase the experience gain of your fleet.
Captain Reania found herself outgunned by a host of Horde ships.  If you assist, she will deploy to the north east to increase the experience gain of your fleet.
A Kraken is floating face down, surrounded by a fleet of Iron Horde ships.  Free it from the Iron Horde grasp and it may be willing to help.
A Kraken is floating face down, surrounded by a fleet of Iron Horde ships.  Free it from the Iron Horde grasp and it may be willing to help.
The Iron Horde discovered an abandoned airship base south of Nagrand.  If we defend the base, we can launch air support for Tanaan.
The Iron Horde discovered an abandoned airship base south of Nagrand.  If we defend the base, we can launch air support for Tanaan.
An Iron Horde shipment containing maps to treasure, hidden under the sea in Nagrand, is headed through the Tanaan Sea.  If you intercept it, you can use the maps for yourself.

Pick up a shipment of oil from your off-shore oil rig.
Our troops in Tanaan have some more equipment to pick up, but it's not safe to send it alone.  Take a transport and a destoyer out to make the drop.
Our troops in Tanaan have some more equipment to pick up, but it's not safe to send it alone.  Take a transport and a destoyer out to make the drop.
Gul'dan has sent submarine hunter-killers to thwart your mission. Lure them into a trap!
You've located Gul'dan's flagship! Maneuver with the wind to take out her carrier escort...
You've run Gul'dan's flagship aground, but now all her guns are trained toward the sea. Prepare for the worst.
Azsuna appears to be an idyllic island teeming with wildlife. Reports of magical activity in the area, however, suggest that not all is as it sems.

Val'Sharah once stood as the heart of druidism on Azeroth, the mighty world tree Shaladrassil standing tall at its center. There are sure to be long-lost secrets hidden in its thickets that would be useful against the Legion.

Highmountain is all that stands of the range that once divided Suramar from the northern lands. Rumor has it that the leader of an ancient tauren tribe on the lonely mountain's slopes wields a relic of legendary power.
Once grazing land for the beasts of the Suramar elves, the bluffs of Stormheim now serve as the capital of an ancient race of Vrykul that fled the northern lands after the Great Sundering.
Our scouts report seeing a knight trapped by a horde of demons. Destroy the demons and bring our brother in arms home.
The forces of Nightmare are closing in on a sacred moonwell. We can't let it fall into darkness.
A Fel Lord may be building up forces in the harsh northern bluffs.
There is a powerful beacon of the Light somewhere in Stormheim. We should find it.
The Legion is planning to launch a coastal assault on Stormheim. We need to find out where.
We've heard whispers that a demon has been offering the Highmountain tauren dark power.
There is a powerful beacon of the Light somewhere in Highmountain. We should find it.
A captured imp told us his masters were planning to attack a Highmountain tauren village - we need to figure out which one.
Description of test mission 1
Description of test mission 2
Description of test mission 3
We can go after the heavy hitters later, right now we need someone who has seen everything. There is one that has been in every war for the past few decades and can do more than kill.

The only way to strengthen our order is through continued focus and training. There is an ancient master who may be willing to share his martial secrets. Seek him out and train with him, and return stronger and wiser.
We will need to recruit a master summoner to assist the Council. A warlock of a notable family was rumored to be spotted in Dalaran.
We believe we can lure a worthwhile rogue into our order with the right... motivation.
The mages of Dalaran seem trustworthy... but are they?
Akazamzarak knows where he can find a whole city of mages, so long as you don't mind the smell.
The Demon invasion has begun.
The Naga have secrets, seek them out.
A sea giant is running rampant, lets hope size doesnt matter.

Demons have invaded Azsuna en masse!  Reinforcements are required immediately to counter this threat.
Black Rook must fall, send our forces to weaken their defenses.
Among the trees of Val'sharah a number of enemies lie in wait.
The swamps outside Bradensbrook are wailing.  See whats causing the noise, and silence it.
Harpies in the Haglands have started raiding our nearby camps for supplies.
The murlocs have made a foothold in the wrecks at Shipwreck Cove.  Clear them out.
The Feltotems at Torok's Bluff are assaulting our troops as they make passage through the pass.  Show them the error of their ways.
The troops are in need of a feast to reward them for their efforts.  Lets get some Goat on the menu.
The Tideskorn are have made a push to new areas of Stormheim, and its not appreciated.  Take care of them.

Name_lang: Assault on the Gates of Valor
Description_lang: The time has come to clear out the demon forces at the gates of Valor.  Ready your best.
Demons have invaded Stormheim en masse!  Reinforcements are required immediately to counter this threat.
Demons have invaded Highmountain en masse!  Reinforcements are required immediately to counter this threat.
Demons have invaded Val'sharah en masse!  Reinforcements are required immediately to counter this threat.
Demons have invaded Suramar en masse!  Reinforcements are required immediately to counter this threat.
Demons have invaded Broken Shore en masse!  Reinforcements are required immediately to counter this threat.
99.0 [reuse me]
We lost contact with the monks at Tian Monastery. We should send Chen Stormstout to investigate.
We've encountered a tribe of hostile Tideskorn vrykul and are under attack. These are the same enemies who kidnapped our allies!
99.0 [reuse me]
We made camp near a field of graves, but at night, apparitions rose and attacked!
The Tideskorn slipped away. We made camp for the night, but the howls of wild beasts echo across the valleys. Stay alert!

Name_lang: Tracking the Tideskorn: The Gates of Valor
Description_lang: We've tracked the Tideskorn to a large, fortified camp at the Gates of Valor. Find any information we can about the kidnapped prisoners.
Drakes have beset our scouts from the skies. These fearsome dragons are looking for their next meal. Let's try not to be dinner!
99.0 [reuse me]
We made camp at the base of the mountain, but the area is home to hostile ettin. We'll need to fend them off before we make our ascent.
The tauren at Snowblind Mesa are dealing with encroaching drogbar. They've asked for our aid in exchange for shelter.
We are nearing Freya's Spring, but the area is guarded by a drogbar chieftain who calls himself the mountain king. Defeat him and we will gain our prize!
A strange magic seeps from beneath the roots of the world tree, Shaladrassil. We must send our champions to investigate this disturbance.
The hides of the Manascale Basilisks in Suramar hold some... interesting properties.  Recover some for research.
The Nightbornes infiltrations have gone on too long.  Stop them at all costs.
Yet still more demons flood the depths of Suramar.  We must hold them.
The Order of the Broken Temple is established, but we need more. Tianji, a renowned troop trainer in the Ox Style, just sent word that she has been attacked!
99.0 [reuse me]
This high on the mountain, the elements themselves are our greatest enemy. Elementals of wind and ice roam the peaks. Defeat them and press on!
We have lost an important set of missives in the Fel Pits of Faronaar.  Retrieve them.
The academy at Narthalas once held a great library with a wealth of knowledge.  See if you can find it.
The enemy has established an array of casters and are bombarding us with terrible balls of Fel energy.  We need help to counter these attacks!
Use to max level followers
The Burning Legion's minions might have information about where the missing council members are being held. It must be obtained at any cost.
Harpies are spreading their foul curse throughout Highmountain. Death is the only way to ensure the curse won't continue.
Black Rook Assassins are attacking Bradensbrook, killing livestock and stealing crops. Defend the village from these ruthless attackers.
Nightmare imps have taken over Moonclaw Vale, corrupting the once serene glade. Help restore balance by ridding the area of imps.
Dalaran's underbelly has a bit of a rodent problem. Exterminate the pests before they make their way out of the sewers.
A group of poachers are threatening the wildlife in Highmountain. Show them what it's like to be hunted!
Archmage Khadgar is concerned for the safety of Dalaran's citizens. He's asked the Unseen Path to provide protection for the city, discreetly.

Name_lang: Unseen Protection: The Mother of Imps
Description_lang: An imp mother has made Bradensbrook her breeding grounds, birthing countless imps into the nearby fields. Defeat the imp mother before her brood grows.
A wave of infernals have crashed upon the shores of Suramar. They must be stopped before they march inland.
The Legion has launched an invasion on the eastern coast of Stormheim. Our hunters can attack at range from the cliffs, protecting the infantry below.
A clan of cave-dwelling drogbar are pilfering eagle eggs to feed to their fledgling worms. They must be stopped before the great eagle becomes extinct!
The Black Harvest archives contain a vast amount of magical knowledge collected over time. It's possible that within its walls we will find something.
The staff Shinfel used in battle against Cho'gall would be powerful enough to create the soul link, but first we'll need to find it.
We need to find a warlock who excels at summoning greater demons. Scout the city of Dalaran, keeping an eye out for anyone with potential.
Theres a foul smell in the air.
The enemies are continually encroaching on Azsuna.  Seek them out, and destroy them.
We must find our way into Faronaar, but the roads are covered in demons.  Let us see if we can scout out an alternate route.
Theres a Deathscreamer up in the mountains thats keeping us up at night.  Can you help out?
The troops are in need of a feast to reward them for their efforts.  Lets get some Goat on the menu.
The hides of the Manascale Basilisks in Suramar hold some... interesting properties.  Recover some for research.
Black Rook must fall, send our forces to weaken their defenses.
Test
The Ettin need to be erradicated.
Snowmane Village is under attack!  Send reinforcements immediately.
Send some troops toe Candle Rock, and clear out the Bluewax miners there.  We need the resources in that mine.
If we can take control of some drakes, we can take away some air superiority from the Tideskorns.
Deep in a cave on Blackbeak Overlook can be found some very powerful Mushrooms that creates a soothing balm.
Reclaimers in Suramar are performing some curious rituals.  Interrupt them, and try to discover their intentions.
The hides of the Sablehorn provide valuable materials for our troops.
Cleanse the Dreadroot of its Twisted Keepers.
Deep under the trees roots near Shalda'Nir grow some powerful flowers.
The enemies are continually encroaching on Azsuna.  Seek them out, and destroy them.
The Feltotem, led by a vicious Crawliac, are mustering troops.  Hit them before they can strike us.
Bosses are on the loose, stop them.
The hides of the Manascale Basilisks in Suramar hold some... interesting properties.  Recover some for research.
Black Rook must fall, send our forces to weaken their defenses.
A mass of armies are preparing for battle.  Crush them.
Slithering Sliss has eluded our capture for too long.  We have her cornered.
This trio of terrors needs to be dealt with, but it will take everything we can muster.
Its time to take Stili the Salty down.
The paths along the cliffs of Highmountain are beseiged with dangers.
The paths along the cliffs of Highmountain are beseiged with dangers.
The troops are in need of a feast to reward them for their efforts.  Lets get some Goat on the menu.

Take the gates in Stormheim.
We will fight them, no matter where they hide.
