Lady Heretica saturates the infernals of Nath'raxas Hold with Sargerite, dramatically increasing their destructive potential. Put an end to these rituals.
The Legion's Pit Lords siphon Primal Sargerite from the Annihilan Pits. Destroy them and collect this Sargerite for our order.
The Portal Keepers beneath Kil'jaeden's Terrace are necessary for the Legion to quickly reinforce Eredath. Send the Portal Keepers back into the Nether.
Fel corrupters in the Arinor Gardens thrum with sargerite. Dismantle them.
Foul experiments breed stronger demons in the Putrid Laboratory. Eliminating the Antoran Soulshapers would halt their progress.
The Scavenger's Boneyard lay beneath the Legion's garrisons in the Antoran Wastes. Send your champions to waylay Legion patrols traveling between them.
There are remote regions of the Argus Wastes with little Legion presence. Scout the Wastes for any resources untouched by fel corruption.
When Kil'jaeden's ship crashed into Argus, it uncovered a cave network rich with minerals. We have a day to explore nine caverns before the Legion arrives.
Many fragments of Argus floating near Eredath appear untouched by fel corruption. Send your champions to investigate.`
Voidscarred Krokul hoard Argunite in the Ruins of Oranaar for some dark purpose. Uncover their troves.
A great summoning circle calls demons from  the Twisting Nether back to Argus. Dismantle the circle; slow the Legion's reinforcements.
A vortex of power envelops the Spirit Crucible. Lead an incursion against the Eredar Soulflayers tapping into that energy.
Lightforged blacksmiths are willing to outfit our champions. Retrieve the materials necessary for their work.
Alleria has revealed a forgotten Eredar armory. We should send our champions to investigate.
Our champions must be adequately armed to assist Hatuun. Order them to search Krokuun for suitable equipment.
A diversion on the western side of Arathi will provide cover for our troop landing to the east.
This is only a test. If this had been an actual mission, you would have been told what to do, and where to go.
Gallywix's Pride is situated atop Bilgewater Harbor. While the monstrous cannon exists, any assault against Orgrimmar will be impossible. Sabotage the great gun.
Scouts have located a high value Horde target in Drustvar. Eliminate them.
That bridge is a main conduit for Hode Supplies. Disrupting the flow of those supplies is critical to our war effort. Reinforcements are on thier way to relieve you. HOLD THAT POSITION!
The Horde commander responsible for the fall of Silverwind Refuge marches against Astranaar. Show him the Alliance will not give up Ashenvale so easily.
A diversion on the western side of Arathi will provide cover for our troop landing to the east.
Our communications to Stormwind are being disrupted by Horde forces in the area.  Send Falstad to clear out any resistance and open communication with the war back home.
Our communications to Orgrimmar are being disrupted by Alliance forces in the area.  Send Valtrois to clear out any resistance and open communication with the war back home.
A large Alliance army advances on the Crossroads, attempting to cut off Mulgore and Durotar. Send our strongest warriors to meet them.
A group of bandits calling themselves the Sailing Wolves have an outpost in Tiragarde Sound. Send your troops to take it for the Horde!
A Horde army marches north to Lor'danel; Blood Guard Rockrain at the fore. Send our forces to stall his aggression, so the evacuation of Teldrassil can continue.
Forsaken forces under Deathstalker Hayward have captured Fenris Keep. Annihilate the undead to secure Lordamere Lake.
Untold numbers of undead are raised in The Sludge Fields and marched against Gilneas. Send an assault to crush Warden Stillwater's seat of power.
Command wishes to reestablish Fort Triumph. Muster your armies, and send them against Desolation Hold.
Control over the Crossroads would disrupt Horde troop movements throughout Kalimdor. You must capture it for the Alliance.
Maestra's Post controls the pass between Ashenvale and Darkshore. Orux Thrice-Damned is leading an attack to take control of the region. Take him down.
The undead have holed themselves up in Shadowfang Keep, and are developing a new bio-weapon to unleash against Gilneas. Eliminate their chief plaguebringer.
Our intel suggests the Horde have fled into the ruins of Alterac. Send scouts to determine their numbers and fortifications.
Supplies passing between Orgrimmar and the Echo Isles must pass through Razor Hill. Set fire to their storehouses.
Scout the ruins of Theramore Isle to assess its viability as a base. Beware the lingering effects of the mana bomb used in its destruction.
Warsong Lumber Camp supplies the Horde war machine with lumber. Commandeer a Shredder to wreak havoc on their supply lines.
Zoram'gar Outpost is the Horde's only port near Azuremyst Isle. Plant depth charges in the surrounding waters to prevent a naval assault.
Darrowmere River stretches from the Plaguelands to Baradin Bay. Our combat engineers should establish dams to deprive the Horde freedom of movement.
Horde forces out of Tarren Mill are attempting to rebuild Durnholde Keep. Reset their progress by laying explosives.
A great deal of salvage can be found within the remnants of Tiragarde Keep and along the Scuttle Coast. Recover what you can.
Rageroar Battleships shell Northwatch Hold once again. Turn our cannons against them to remove the blockade.
Bael Modan is being threatened by a tauren warband from the north. Stand strong with our dwarven allies.
Tauren warbraves are on the move from Thunder Bluff to the Barrens. Hold them at the Great Gate of Mulgore.
The Horde is showing a renewed interest in Blackfathom Deeps. Send our scouts to investigate what they have discovered, and claim it for the Alliance.
Following the burning of Teldrassil, the Horde are entrenching themselves in northern Darkshore. Eliminate their chief engineer to halt progress.
Sergeant Dontrag leads a Horde assault against Stardust Spire. Eliminating him could sow chaos in the enemy's battle plan. See it done.
The Forsaken mage, Derek the Undying, conducts an arcane ritual in the Dalaran Crater, at the convergence of multiple powerful ley-lines. Put an end to it.
The dark rangers of Undercity conduct a guerilla war from the abandoned town of Strahnbrad. Send our agents to root them out.
The Horde constructs doomsday weapons using Azerite in Orgrimmar. We must discover what they are building before it is too late.
Ratchet plays at neutrality during peace, but serves the Horde in war. Discover the intentions of the Steamwheedle Cartel.
The ancient of war, Big Baobob, requires assistance rebuilding the defenses around the Shrine of Aessina. Send the necessary resources.
Splintertree Post has withstood siege by the Sentinel army for too long. Send reinforcements to demolish the Horde base camp.
The dwarven ghosts of Dun Garok have been mastered by the Forsaken. They send our own fallen comrades against us. Purge the fortress of Horde and spirit alike.
Sentinels from Stardust Spire will soon launch an assault to retake Silverwind Refuge from the Horde. Send our finest to bolster their charge.
A Horde garrison controls Azurelode Mine in southwest Hillsbrad. Send a strike force to seize control of this strategic resource.
Horde reinforcements from the Sepulcher in Silverpine Forest are marching toward Tirisfal under High Executor Hadrec. Halt their advance.
Much of the Horde's naval power is docked in the Echo Isles. Infiltrate the troll capital, and set fire to their ships.
The Deep Elem Mine could be a valuable resource in the war against the Horde in Lordaeron. Set explosives to clear the rubble blocking the mine's entrance.
The blight infecting Southshore is being weaponized by the Horde's apothecaries. Blow their experiments up in their faces.
Goblin salvagers have a new Azerite-powered shredder model dismanting the ruins of Auberdine. Steal or sabotage their tech.
Powerful magic seeps through the Wailing Caverns, transforming the Barrens. Devise a way to leverage that magic for the Alliance.
Lay siege to Hunter's Hill. If we capture it, we will control passage between the Barrens and Stonetalon Mountains.
The dryad Illiyana has rallied her sisters in Forest Song. Their nature magic is destroying our Shredders. Eliminate them all.
Maestra's Post controls the pass between Ashenvale and Darkshore. Moon Priestess Maestra's vigil must end. Bring her down.
Scouts report a Gilnean army under Darius Crowley marches against Hillsbrad. Set upon his forces at the Sludge Fields, where our power is greatest.
An Alliance host marches from Stromgarde towards the ruins of Durnholde keep, to secure Thoradin's wall. Send our mightest warriors to meet them.
The Alliance brazenly attempts to rebuild Tiragarde Keep. Bring our full might down upon them and scour the ruins from Horde lands.
[ph]
Thenysil commands the remaining Sentinels in Ashenvale. Infiltrate Astranaar and take her down before they muster their strength.
Dentaria Silverglade in Lor'danel oversees the evacuation of the Teldrassian survivors to Azuremyst. Slaying her will sow chaos in their ranks.
The Bloodfang Pack controls Fenris Isle. Create a distraction along the Misty Shore to lure them out of position, allowing Horde refugees to escape Tirisfal across the water.
Wildhammer Gryphon Riders patrol Darrowmere River, preventing troop movements. Under the cover of darkness, infiltrate their roost and slay their mounts.
We have reports of Alliance ships off the Scuttle Coast. Investigate their numbers and their intentions.
Alliance forces sabotaged Gallywix's Pride, the great gun above Bilgewater Harbor. See it repaired to secure Bladefist Bay.
The Zoram'gar Docks will be vital for any assault against Azuremyst Isle. Plant depth charges to prevent any naval assault by the Alliance.
Plaguebringer Harris has developed a new bio-weapon. Unleash his plague on the 7th legion forces surrounding Shadowfang Keep.
The ruins of Alterac could be repaired to serve as a defensible base of operations for the Horde in Lordaeron. Send forces to see the work done.
Northwatch Hold relies on superior firepower to keep our forces at bay. Install goblin Azerite cannons on the northern shore of the Great Divide.
There is usable salvage within the battlescar of the southern barrens. Recover what you can. Avoid the dwarves of Bael Modan.
The Alliance is using Bael Modan as a staging point against Mulgore. Purge their armies from the Barrens.
Taurajo has lain in ruins long enough. March our warriors against the Alliance soldiers who siege the Great Gate. Punish the Alliance looters.
Alliance soldiers continue pouring into Ashenvale, reinforcing their holdings. Investigate Stardust Spire for any weaknesses.
New Azerite-powered shredders devised by our goblin allies are salvaging the ruins of Auberdine. Prevent any Alliance spies from gathering information.
The Alliance is showing a renewed interest in Blackfathom Deeps. Send our scouts to investigate what they have found there.
An army of Alliance soldiers from the Plaguelands marches towards Hillsbrad. Attack from the shadows to slow their progress.
A human mage, High Sorceror Andromath, conducts an arcane ritual in the Dalaran Crater, at the convergence of multiple powerful ley-lines. Put an end to it.
The vengeful night elves have recalled their forces stationed throughout Kalimdor, to begin a campaign against Orgrimmar. Track their movements across the continent.
The Steamwheedle Cartel will not openly declare for the Horde, but provides a vital stream of supplies. Prevent the Alliance from discovering these smuggling operations.
Night elves streaming out of Darnassus pose a threat to Shatterspear Vale. Construct defenses in the nearby war camp to protect our troll allies.
The dwarves of Ironforge marshal their forces to retake Dun Garok. Drive them back through Thoradin's Wall.
The kal'dorei siege our outposts across Ashenvale. Splintertree Post must not be allowed to fall. Send reinforcements.
Huntress Jalin leads her Sentinels against Silverwind Refuge, attempting to retake it for the Alliance. Throw them back.
Our garrison in control of the Azurelode Mine has come under assault. We must not lose control of this vital source of ore.
With the fall of Lordaeron, the Alliance has set its sights on Silverpine Forest. Defend the Sepulcher against encroaching forces.
Alliance raids against the Echo Isles are damaging our ability to supply the Eastern Kingdoms warfront. Construct greater defenses around our largest port.
Gnomish explosives line the walls of Deep Elem Mine. They must be cleared out so mining operations can continue.
A cadre of paladins under Raleigh the Devout attempts to purify the ruins of Southshore. Provoke the blighted creatures there to disrupt his efforts.
An ancient of war allied with the Sentinels stands vigil over the Shrine of Aessina. Burn it to the ground.
Powerful magic seeps through the Wailing Caverns, transforming the Barrens. Devise a way to leverage that magic for the Horde.
The Alliance cannot hold Honor's Stand without supplies. Lay siege and starve them out.
A pack of dire wolves have been stalking Wolf's Den. Rexxar should be able to track and tame the beasts for the outpost.
Test Mission
Scout the ruins of Theramore Isle to assess its viability as a base. Beware the lingering effects of the mana bomb used in its destruction.
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost on Vigil Hill, but it is currently guarded by the local militia. Dispatch a war party to clear them out!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Drustvar, but it is currently infested with wicker beasts. Dispatch a war party to clear the area!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Drustvar. Dispatch a war party to secure the area.
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost on Windwhisper Summit, but the cave is home to a man-eating grizzly. Dispatch a hunting party to slay the beast!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Stormsong Valley, but it is currently occupied by the enemy. Dispatch a war party to claim Hillcrest Pasture for the Horde!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Stormsong Valley, but it is currently occupied by the enemy. Dispatch a war party to claim Stonetusk Watch for the Horde!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Zuldazar, but it is currently occupied by the enemy. Dispatch your troops to take Veiled Grotto for the Alliance!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Zuldazar, but it is currently occupied by a tribe of wild gorillas. Dispatch a hunting party to clear the camp for the Alliance!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Zuldazar, but it is currently occupied by the enemy. Dispatch your troops to take Verdant Hollow for the Alliance!
Horde agents in Tiragarde are funneling resources to Freehold and Southport, in a shadow war against Boralus. Find and assault their base.
The Horde sends its fliers over Boralus Harbor, probing for weakness. Send our technicians to improve the city's anti-air cannons.
The Bilgewater Cartel is making a play for the Azerite that has been discovered in Arom's Crossing. Locate their base of operations.
Goblin machinery is tearing through the mountains of Drustvar, harvesting Azerite. Destroy their machines.
Brennadam is under siege! An Azerite weapon is bombarding the town from the Dire Hills. Launch an assault against the Horde position.
Warfang Hold is a well-established Horde base in Stormsong. Scout their capabilities, and sabotage their supply caches.
Remnants of the Twilight's Hammer operate within Blackfathom, harvesting Azerite from the planet. Eliminate them, and secure the Azerite.
Azerite flows through the Wailing Caverns in tremendous quantities. Do not allow it to fall into the wrong hands of Azeroth's enemies.
Set fire to the Horde's bestiaries near the Grove of the Ancients in Darkshore. Without their wolves, the Horde will be unable to field raiders to send against us.
The animals of the Overgrowth have been behaving strangely since Azerite was discovered in the Wailing Caverns. Capture several species for research.
The 7th legion fleet that failed to apprehend Talanji has begun constructing a base near their landing site. Send a garrison to drive them into the sea.
The Alliance has established a base on Zuldazar, and is reinforcing using Dark Iron mole machines. Sabotage their tunnels and break their machines.
Deep in the Nazmir swamplands, the Alliance is attempting to create a foothold. Find their fledgling base and report back to command.
The Alliance is supplying its troops in Nazmir from Fort Victory, deep within Nazmani territory. Waylay one of their caravans and salvage any usable supplies.
Alliance ships are moored near Shatterstone Harbor, off the coast of Vol'dun. Launch an assault before the Alliance gains another foothold on Zandalar.
Gnomish flying machines have been seen flying above Vol'dun. Discover their launching pad.
Night elf hippogryphs roost in Shatterspear Vale. Send a strike force to eliminate this base, and ensure Horde aerial superiority over Darkshore.
The animals of the Overgrowth have been behaving strangely since Azerite was discovered in the Wailing Caverns. Capture several species for research.
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Zuldazar, but it is currently occupied by the enemy. Dispatch your troops to take Mistvine Ledge for the Alliance!
One of our supply planes crashed in Nazmir. We need to send a rescue party to secure the crash site before our supplies fall into enemy hands!
Our scouts have found an ideal location for an outpost in Vol'dun, but it is currently occupied by the enemy. Dispatch your troops to take Vulture's Nest for the Alliance!
The outpost at Stonetusk Watch has requested materials to build a scrapping machine. Dispatch a war party to salvage the necessary materials from enemy engineers!
The outpost at Stonetusk Watch has been having issues with ettins in the woods. Dispatch a hunting party to eliminate the threat!
The druids at Swiftwind Post are seeking information concerning ancient Drust rituals. Dispatch a scouting party to search for clues!
The outpost at Mudfisher Cove is under attack by wicker beasts. Dispatch reinforcements to protect our troops!
The outpost at Grimwatt's Crash is under attack by blood trolls! Dispatch reinforcements to aid in the defense!
A vital supply shipment for the outpost at Vulture's Nest has been intercepted by bandits. Dispatch a team to recover the stolen supplies!
Zuldazar is home to a variety of dinosaur species that have not been encountered elsewhere. Dispatch a team of hunters to capture specimens for research!
The outpost at Mugamba Overlook has requested materials to build a scrapping machine. Dispatch a war party to salvage the necessary materials from enemy engineers!
The outpost at Mistvine Ledge has requested healing support. Dispatch a team to safely escort the reinforcements to the outpost!
We require a Mission Command Table at the Great Seal, however the locals are being unaccomodating. Send some representatives to convince them.
Send your followers to collect and make an offering to the Loa's, hopefully this will empower the Boons they bestow upon you.
Send your followers to rescue the Caravan Master who was taken prisoner by the Faithless.
Send your followers to Stormsong in search of the parts needed to repair the Harvester.
Send your followers to Castaway Point and assist Dynamite Jack to install a cannon.
Send your followers to Drustvar to seek a blessing from the Order of Embers.
Send your followers to the location on the treasure map. This will be dangerous, but likely very lucrative.

Name_lang: Treasure Map: Mysteries of the Reef
Description_lang: Send your followers to the location on the treasure map. This will be dangerous, but likely very lucrative.
Send your followers to the location on the treasure map. This will be dangerous, but likely very lucrative.

Send your followers to the location on the treasure map. This will be dangerous, but likely very lucrative.
Send your followers to investigate.
Send your followers to investigate.
Deploy spies to Warfang Hold to follow up on rumors of increased Horde activity in the area.
Bring the Swift Vengeance to Chandlery Wharf and leave it there under the guise of a pirate's prize.
Silas Darkmoon has announced a corn dog eating contest. You're far too busy, but the prize pool sounds enticing.
It was a time of great desperation, as the evil dragon aspect Deathwing the Destroyer returned with sundering fury. Send your followers to revisit this era.
The fog shrouded Pandaria finally cleared, and we discovered a new way to live slowly yet meaningfully, and lay many inner demons to rest.
Responding to the onslaught of Scourge assaults, we banded together. With our very lives on the line, we faced an evil we had not before withheld, and triumphed.
The Dark Portal opened, we stood ready to launch through and defend our homes against the inevitable assault of the Legion.
Falling into the depths of history, we made new allies, and confronted our past.
A finely written letter has arrived asking for your best behaved followers to attend a celebration in their honor. Hopefully theres presents.
Who doesn't love a good egg hunt?
There is much debate among your followers regarding which brew at brewfest is the hoppiest. Send them to find out once and for all!
So many fires to light, not enough time! Get your followers on the task to help out.
Something strange is going on, something's wrong, you're not going to investigate, send those followers to illuminate.
Even followers need love! I wonder if they will bring you back something nice?
The feasting tables have been spread with wonderful arrays of cuisine. It's only fair you thank your followers for their efforts by sending them to partake.
The Alathir Spire is ripe with enemy creatures. Send our forces to thin their ranks.
Send a crew to retrieve whatever they can from the wreckage of our ships.
Some fool decided to rewire and upgrade a scraphound. He even named it!
We have detected a large enemy force moving through our lines. Wipe them out.
We have heard reports of a "thumping" coming from under the sea in this area.
A storm is coming, but we must deploy reinforcements.
Our lines are being raided, we will drop anchor here and destroy all who approach.
We've recovered a barely functional vessel. We are going to load it with explosives and aim it at the enemy. Just don't forget to jump..
Nothing quite as satisfying as shooting goblins out the side cannons, except when they have bombs to drop on their way!
Fog is setting in, send a small force to destroy what they can under its cover.
Theres so many of them it's like shooting fish in a barrel! Only it's Murlocs!
Send our crews to explore the newly revealed landmass.
A malfunctioning robot has decided it is actually a troll and started gathering followers.
Nothing like a good bit of engineering to really spice up the local wildlife!
One of the vessels we thought was lost has managed to send a distress call.
Who in their right mind would make a mechanical spider?
A container drone has decided the best way to complete its delivery is to ensure the crate lands right on the heads of the recipient.
Scrapbots are running rampant, deal with it.
Send your followers to the location on the treasure map. Zem'lan left guards, yet that was many milenia ago.

An Alliance general has been tasked with carrying vital information on the next Worldvein location to Theramore for transport to Stormwind. We are going to stage a raid on the Southern Barrens as a pretense to steal the information.
A Horde general has been tasked with delivering information on the location of a new Worldvein to Ogrimmar. We are going to stage a raid on Durotar and in the melee steal that information.
The captured documents point to a special artifact from the Uldir facility that can be used as a compass to find the Worldvein.
The captured documents point to a special artifact from the Uldir facility. It turns out we had it within our grasp the whole time.

Now that we have the compass we are ready to proceed with the expedition to find the next Worldvein. Based on the bearing it appears we must venture deep into uncharted seas, prepare for a long expedition.
Send your followers to the location noted on the map. We have word Alliance spies have gotten wind of the location, it is now a race.
Send your followers to the location noted on the map. We have word Horde spies have gotten wind of the location, it is now a race.
Send your followers to the location noted on the map. We have word Horde spies have gotten wind of the location, it is now a race.
The problem has gotten even worse, and rogue Skeletons have run amok in a giant swarm. Snuff them out, and you will have my thanks!
A pack of verdant prowlers have gone wild and are savaging the Garden of Night. Put them down.
A noble ancient has gone berserk due to anima starvatation. Lay them to rest with dignity.
The source of the Swarming Skeletons has become clear, as a Necromancer raises his grim visage in support of his minions. Crush their defiance at once!
You've enraged the leader of the pack and he's joined his cohorts.
A small number of skeletons have run amok in the Bone Pits. Disposing of them should be a simple task.
More skeletons are breaking free in the wake of the accident at the Bone Pits. Break them up.
Suppressing the Verdant Prowler population has infuriated Erezuel, and he seeks revenge.
A group of anima smugglers are attemping to steal anima rations from the deserving. End them.
The Gorm are once again draining anima from the land. Eliminate them.
A massive pack of Gorm is rampaging across the earth. Lay them to rest.
This proud goliath has been co-opted by the Forsworn and turned against us. Restrain him as best you can.
The leader of the hive is causing no end of issues. Terminate him with prejudice.
Juvenile Miredeer have run amok, and are damaging the plants.
A group of Rotbriar Scrappers are causing trouble.
The Darkwarren has been completely overrun. Beat back the Gorm.
A Rotbriar Trickster and some Scrappers have ganged up to accomplish their nefarious objectives.
The Tricksters are going berserk and playing harmful pranks. Stop them.
Juvenile Miredeer and Runedeer are sparring and tearing up the earth. Suppress them.
A group of Possessed Sylvar has been found roaming the woods.
A swarm of Gormling are razing the fields. Drive them back.
Deifir has overcome his pride and retained allies in his fight. I wish you luck.
A pair of Gormling Harriers are organizing a larger group of Nibblers. Nip this in the bud.
A group of Runestags have claimed turf and are driving out other animals.
A group of dangerous Brittlebark Manifestations was sighted. Hunt them down.
Erezuel is taking more Miredeer than can be sustained. Stop him again.
A deadly group of Forest Shriekers is disturbing the night. Stop them.
A Runelight Leaper is being menaced by a horde of Verdant Prowlers. Rescue and befriend it.
A deadly group of Possessed Scavengers and Faeries are slaying all who pass.
You've dealt with many of the Darkwarren. Now deal with their Matriarch to claim one of her own for yourself!
The Etherwyrms have built up to unsustainable numbers. Bring them to a reasonable end.
Emotions have coalesced Pride into physical form. It's attacking the order of things. Remedy this problem.
A group of Forsworn Ascended have positioned themselves defensively, blocking up the pass. Root them out.
A brace of Umbral Phalanx are menacing our flank. Drive them back!
A swarm of Misled Stewards are constructing dark artifacts to arm the forces. Bring them to their senses.
Dark Master Vaalgryn and his pupils are conducting a ritual. Stop it at once!
A sect of Scholars has turned their expertise to harness innocent souls. This perversion of justice cannot stand.
Etherwyrms are still devoring all the anima they can find. Restore the balance.
Some untouched souls are trapped by a group of Clawguards. Rescue them and return them at once.
Forsworn forces continue to harry our forces and threaten the peace. Pacify them.
Animated Prowlers have gone berserk and are menacing the Stewards. Shut them down.
Glimmerflies have overrun the fields and are stripping the plants bare. Retrieve their wings and render them to gold.
Doubt itself has obtained physical form and is tormenting the Ascended. Drive it off!
Led by a Converted Praetor, a large band of Forsworn have hidden in a temple. They must be stopped.
A giant Colossus has trapped a Skyfoal in a cave. Extricate the poor creature with haste.
A Forsworn Overseer and his Punishers have stolen a large mass of anima. Can you retrieve it?
The Forsworn War-Captain has returned, with a Gracefallen Tactician, and his Forsworn. Can you stop them?
A pair of Callused Monstrosities have slipped loose of their handlers and are shredding the bone supplies. Bring them home.
War Wraiths have gone mad, attacking anything that comes near them. Lay them to rest.
A brace of Bonewrought Thrashers wreak havoc and slice anything that comes near them.
Stitched Defenders are protecting the Guarded Defilers as they do their work. End them both.
A large group of Neonate Bonetooths are seeking to prove their worth in the ruins below. Disillusion them.
Steelspine Vanguards and Wallbreakers have been seen threatening a necropolis. Snuff it out.
In an ineffectual attempt to cleanse a Wraith Vanguard, a group of Necromantic Scourers have instead enraged the fearsome foe. Bring order to them.
A glop of Green Slimes have coalesced around an anima crystal to the south. Cleanse them at once.
An imbecilic apprentice has panicked the Necrorays into a hasty migration. Prevent them from leaving and harvest their corpses.
A group of Monstrosities has have been identified at this location. Prevent them from causing too much damage.
The Warden of Rituals and his Ritualists have risen once more, seeking to avenge his fate. Remind them of their place.
A pungent pit provides putrescent presence. Purge them!
The remnants of war can always be re-used. Extract what value you can from the Wraiths and Repurposed Parts, and bring it to me.
Bonebreaker Moroc is hoarding anima and slowing production. Retrieve it at any cost, but beware the dangers that await.
Befouler Ahnqat is raising dark hordes of enemies. Bring her down.
Nirvaska has harnessed the power of a Fleshcrafted Juggernaut. Bring them to heel.
Not one, but two Corpselouse Mothers and a host of Spawnlings are burrowed into this hill. Root them out and you will be rewarded handsomely.
A fright of Terrorwings is roosting on one of the towers. Drive them out.
Horrific Bonemaulers are uprooting corpses. Remedy this unseemly disorder.
The Riftkeepers are neglecting their duties and causing a raucous ruckus. Can you remedy that?
Callous Peacekeepers continue to bedevil the residents. Drive them back.
Cruel Collectors have banded together to extract anima from those less powerful. Protect the weak!
A group of Privileged Contributors are throwing an underground party. This affront cannot be allowed.
Terrowings continue to menace the area. Deal with them before they roost!
Depraved Caregivers are shirking their duty by imprisoning souls rather than curating them. Rescue the souls!
A group of nobles are trying to steal some of our anima supplies. Thwart them.
Soulflayers have struck back, enlisting Stalkers to protect them. Show them no mercy.
Archives Investigators are concealing important information about anima reserves. Extract it from them.
A group of Carved Trackers is moving to capture valuable goods they've found. Waylay them!
Stacka refuses to cooperate. Show him the error of his ways.
A Bonemauler Alpha has chivvied a group of Horrific Bonemaulers into a ferocious force. This cannot stand.
Charthox once again stands proud, freed from his restraints. Make him grovel.
Big Shiny has rallied some dredgers and stolen anima. Restrain him and retrieve the precious energy.
Archivist Ionata and her schemes must be unwound. Unravel the threads.
Crucible Seekers and Mawsworn Interceptors patrol the entrance, hungry to inflict agonies upon the unwary.
Ghelak the Incarcerator is doing unspeakable things to the poor souls in his grasp.
Your power obligates us to gamble on rescuing who we can from this horrific place. Bring down the Stygia Coalescence and bring them home.
Stygian Giants are guarding a mysterious object. Help us defeat them and invoke the power of the Waystone to bring our companions to safety.
Mawsworn Vanquishers darken the skies and prevent further advance. With your power and knowledge, we shall prevail!
Dravok the Chainwarden and a cohort of Mawsworn Soulweavers are performing dark rituals that must be stopped at any cost.
The Grand Automaton inside Perdition Hold threatens the tenuous balance we've carved out in the Maw. We must stop it at any cost.
Return, if you can.
Dolos has marshalled Winged Automatons and is tormenting innocents in the depths of Perdition Hold. Dull the blade of Death.
Master Shadeweaver is braiding the very souls of innocents into grotesque abominations at the Altar of Domination. Stop him and the Conquerors protecting him.
Krala has gathered a host of Spectral Assassins. Clip her wings and bring an end to the misery.
A herd of Swift Skymanes got spooked by a Copperfur Lurker. Calm them all.
Ash Ghouls are being driven out of control by the searing pain, attacking anything nearby. Put them down.
The Briarbane are still in open revolt. Teach them a lesson in humility.
We still haven't managed to get the animated sinstones under control. Please see to it immediately.
We have cornered another Sinstone Hoarder. Go claim our anima!
It is time to break the back of the Briarbane! Their continued resistance is unacceptable.
The Warstitched Surgeons are going to far with their creations. Time for these abominations to be driven out.
He is a mighty foe, but you are mightier. Strike him down, and show no mercy.
The abberations in the Sepulcher of Knowledge are splitting uncontrollably. Deal with them.
The Baron rises, and we must rise to the challenge. Seek out Baron Halis in the House of Constructs.
We need to learn more about what is going on around the Necrotic Wake. Scout it out.
Unstable memory fragments and worse challenges still plague the Acolytes, and cast doubt. Restore their confidences by dealing with them.
The Cloudfeather Guardian has become agitated. Pacify it and remove the Etherwyrms causing it distress.
Dive deeper into the Necrotic Wake, and clear a path for what is to come.
Disrupt the Drust's effort to taint Ardenweald by terminating the Possessed.
